      "message": "I don\u0027t know if this acts differently with the ansible_runner.get_inventory method.  But the above ansible-inventory command doesn\u0027t return a non-zero on error\n\n```\n[root@okd-master-0 ~]# ansible-inventory --list -i /etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory \n[WARNING]:  * Failed to parse /etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory with yaml plugin: We were unable to read either as JSON\nnor YAML, these are the errors we got from each: JSON: Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)  Syntax Error while\nloading YAML.   found unexpected \u0027:\u0027  The error appears to be in \u0027/etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory\u0027: line 7, column 12,\nbut may be elsewhere in the file depending on the exact syntax problem.  The offending line appears to be:\n[beaker_sut:foo]            ^ here\n[WARNING]:  * Failed to parse /etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory with ini plugin: /etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory:7: Section\n[beaker_sut:foo] has unknown type: foo\n[WARNING]: Unable to parse /etc/dci-rhel-agent/inventory as an inventory source\n[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available\n{\n    \"_meta\": {\n        \"hostvars\": {\n            \"jumpbox\": {\n                \"ansible_host\": \"localhost\",\n                \"ansible_ssh_private_key_file\": \"/etc/dci-rhel-agent/secrets/id_rsa\",\n                \"ansible_user\": \"root\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"all\": {\n        \"children\": [\n            \"ungrouped\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"ungrouped\": {\n        \"hosts\": [\n            \"jumpbox\"\n        ]\n    }\n}\n[root@okd-master-0 ~]# echo $?\n0\n\n```\n\nWhich is why I asked if you had a negative test case for this PR.",
