      "side": 1,
      "message": "I disagree, the example does not contradict what the PR states to do :(\n1. I never said it returned a non-zero code, but it prints an error message on stderr\n2. the code returns an error if there\u0027s an error message on stderr.\n3. the ansible_runner wrapper does not check the return code, but returns stdout and stderr\nhttps://github.com/ansible/ansible-runner/blob/devel/src/ansible_runner/interface.py#L715\n4. Hence, the code checks the stderr output, not return code since upstream doesn\u0027t use it (IMHO, bad design but we have to deal with it)\n\nAnsible-inventory is limited in what kind of errors it can detect and I\u0027m aware of that. If we want to detect more advanced error, we need a more advanced tool like ansible-lint, or write a specific inventory linting tool.",
